		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Republic of Ireland is a country on an island NorthWest of Europe. The only border it shares is with Northern Ireland to its north. Ireland was inhabited by the Celtic tribes in the 5th century BCE. The Celts ran Ireland in small kingdoms for the next millennia. In 432 AD Saint Patrick arrived in the area. Saint Patrick was a Roman-British missionary who brought Christianity to the Celts living in
 
Ireland. He helped convert the local Celts into Christianity. Creation of Monasteries during this time helped scholars gain and keep the knowledge of Latin and Greek as well as metal works. In 795 the Vikings invaded Ireland attacking monasteries and towns. The Vikings stayed for over a couple of hundred years until the Normans arrived in the 12th century. In 1171 King Henry II of England claimed Ireland as a part of his empire. Even though Ireland was dominated by England for the next few hundred years, they rebelled and fought against it many times with the help of the Scottish and then with the help of the French. Finally in 1800 Ireland officially became a part of United Kingdom.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
