		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				In 1919 the Irish rebels called the Sinn Fein declared independence from England and thus causing separation from Northern Ireland following the signing of the Anglo-Irish Treaty. The treaty caused a divide between the old IRA (Irish Republican Army) members. This led to a civil war between pro-treaty supporters and anti-treaty supporters. The war and its outcome caused a deep divide in Ireland and the two political parties Fine Gael and Fianna Fail in Republic of Ireland are direct descendants of the opposing sides of the civil war. After the civil war the independent state was eventually declared a free republic.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
