		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today Republic of Ireland is the third most developed country, and ranks tenth wealthiest country in the world. Ireland is a member of the European Union and Council of Europe.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Geographically Ireland is covered by water with North Sea to the North, the Irish Sea to the East, the Atlantic Ocean to the West, and the Celtic Sea to the South. Western Ireland is more rugged terrain than the east. The highest mountain is Carrauntoohil at 1000 meters (3400 feet) high. There are many lakes and rivers in the lowlands in Ireland, the longest river is the River Shannon. Ireland is the least forested country in all of Europe because of clearing all the trees to make space for crop lands. The climate in Ireland is mild and wet. The winters are mild, summers are cool, over cast and rainy more than half of the year.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
