				Shamrock, a three leaved clover, is a symbol of the “luck of the Irish”. It was first used by Saint Patrick to teach people about the Christian Holy Trinity of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit. It was later taken up by rival militias during 18th century political unrests. During the 19th and 20th century the use of the shamrock became more frequent eventually leading to world wide association with the Irish culture.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
	
		
		
